
AWS / Laravel / Ubuntu / nix* / Nginx

Project:
--------
    * Add Remote Server (AWS Server)
        * Server Type: (Prod / Staging)
        * Add PEM file
            Path
        
        * Add User (login user)

        * Add Web Server type (Nginx)
            * Web Server configuration path (/etc/nginx)
        
    * Add Remote Workspace (Remote Directory)
        * Mode: (Prod / Staging) (Cannot switch mode on remote)
        * Remote Server
        * Directory -> Site Name
        * Git Repo + Branch

    * Add Local Workspace (Local Directory)
        * Mode: (Prod / Staging) (User can switch mode on local)
        * Directory -> Site name
        * Git Repo + Branch

    One above is added, we can link local workspace to remote workspace


Modules:
--------
    * Local Git module
        * commit
        * status
        * push
        * switch branch
        * show branch

    * Remote Git module
        * pull

    * Server module 
        * run commands

    * FTP Module
        * fetch / Edit / Remove files
    
    * SCP Module
        * Copy Files

    * CLI Log Reader (Read and parse logs from the CLI)


Future:
-------
    Server Monitoring (install agent on the server)